abstract: Sure, it’s way too early to be thinking about running-mate pairings. But what the heck.

lead_paragraph: It would be ridiculous to imagine running-mate pairings this early for Democrats in the 2020 presidential race.

headline_main: Jeffrey Epstein, India, the Fed: Your Thursday Briefing

abstract: As Democrats embrace the idea of expanding the federal health insurance program, we looked at what it covers and costs. It’s far from “free.”
snippet: As Democrats embrace the idea of expanding the federal health insurance program, we looked at what it covers and costs. It’s far from “free.”
lead_paragraph: Medicare, the federal health insurance program for people who are 65 or older, has become something of a panacea in the Democratic presidential race.

abstract: With Joseph R. Biden Jr., Kamala Harris, and Cory Booker all onstage, candidates are likely to make direct appeals to the Democratic Party’s most loyal constituency.
snippet: With Joseph R. Biden Jr., Kamala Harris, and Cory Booker all onstage, candidates are likely to make direct appeals to the Democratic Party’s most loyal constituency.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT — While the first night of the second round of Democratic debates showed off the party’s ideological diversity, the second night will look more like the Democratic base.

headline_main: At Tonight’s Democratic Debate, Black Voters Will Be the Focus

abstract: The self-help author had some standout moments in Tuesday’s Democratic debate, and the right propped her up as a way to portray the whole field as wacky and unserious.
snippet: The self-help author had some standout moments in Tuesday’s Democratic debate, and the right propped her up as a way to portray the whole field as wacky and unserious.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — If you asked President Trump’s supporters who won Tuesday night’s Democratic primary debate, their first answer — unequivocally — was Mr. Trump. But they also expressed a surprising, if not always entirely sincere, admiration for Marianne Williamson, the author and self-help guru who set herself apart with warnings of a “dark psychic force” tearing the country apart and an attack on “wonkiness” as the proper antidote to the populist president.

headline_main: Moderates Faltered at Tuesday’s Debate. Will Joe Biden Do Better Tonight?

abstract: Senators Elizabeth Warren and Bernie Sanders formed an ideological tag team during the second round of Democratic presidential debates by embracing their liberal policy goals amid an intraparty fight with moderates over health care.

headline_main: Warren and Sanders Fight Back Against Criticism From Moderates

abstract: The real victor in the moderates-versus-progressives battle was the moderate who wasn’t there.
snippet: The real victor in the moderates-versus-progressives battle was the moderate who wasn’t there.
lead_paragraph: Marianne Williamson won last night’s debate if you judge exclusively in terms of charisma, rhetoric and the effective use of television. Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren won last night’s debate — Sanders slightly more so, in my view — if you judge based on whether the two most important candidates onstage did what they needed to remain important. John Delaney won last night’s debate, despite earning the everlasting ire of left-wing Twitter, if you want to know which also-ran candidate made the most of his chances in the spotlight.
